<AUTHOR>kretara</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>We bought the van used with 24k miles on it, now have 41k on it. My wife loves the van and we both love the stow and go seating. The versatility of a pick-up in a van. Just finished 1,200 mile trip with no problems. MPG: 16 city, 24 highway. The van has been in the shop a few times for warranty issues. The torque converter has been replaced, the transmission was flashed with new software, brakes and tires @30k, clunking front suspension, both power doors failing to open. The van should be more reliable, but what can one expect from an American car. </TEXT>
<FAVORITE>stow-in-go seating, trip computer, hauling capacity and long distance comfort.</FAVORITE>
