<DATE>05/11/2008</DATE>
<AUTHOR>ps</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Have owned this van for about 16 months and put about 18000 miles on it. Needed service once for a rusted brake line for ABS (ABS light came on and stayed on). Has been dependable and very versatile. The convenience and ease of stow and go seating is great, as is the power lift gate. The remote start is a must for me in the winter. Gas mileage is just OK, not horrible at 20-21 mpg mixed city and highway driving after employing gas saving driving tips (set your cruise control at 60 mph on the highway (city speed limit) and watch other cars pass you like you are standing still!), got 18mpg consistently before that. Transmission "thunks" downshifting, jerking the van, not at all smooth. </TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Stow and go seating, power lift gate, remote start, storage. Radio and HVAC controls convenient for me. </FAVORITE>
